I asked (Finnish singer-songwriter) Mirel Wagner to record  an a cappella to set against our track. She crushed it. Will it appear  in the movie? I donâ€™t want to say. At this stage, I just want people to  get a whiff of this movieâ€¦ thereâ€™s something in this film thatâ€™s very  Lotus-eaters. The place itself is very seductive, this sanitarium. Itâ€™s  about absolution in a way. The diagnosis itself is what keeps people  from leaving. It allows you to avoid taking responsibility; itâ€™s like  having a note from your doctor, and who doesnâ€™t want that? That I Wanna  Be Sedated track is about letting yourself goâ€¦ losing your purchase on  reality. Thatâ€™s the horror of the place."

text: This movie is very well thought up and very well made. this is something that i have not seen in a mystery/horror film. i think this movie was more of a horror film than anything else. and i say that for it's creepy aspects and it's supernatural themes. i won't go into any details don't want to spoil it for the other readers but whoever saw this movie knows what i'm talking about. it is an unusual film but that's what i like about it. you don't come across these types of movies everyday. so when they come ya gotta snatch them up. what entices me about this movie is that it's something that has not been done yet or in a long time. it's not the same old story. the acting was amazing in this movie and the directing was good and the music was amazing and creepy. this is a great movie. if you have not seen this movie then i recommend you do. this movie is cinematastic rating 5/5

text: The footage of this film is amazing. The landscape of the Swiss Alps (in reality took place in Germany), along with the beautiful camera and sound work - gave this whole movie a deep mediation aroma. Music soundtrack was also well fitting in. As for the plot? Meh... But even though the characters and plot were mediocre at best,  the actors themselves brought meaningful moments, and kept the mystery of the thriller pretty suspenseful and interesting. Would definitely recommend watching it! 7/10 in my book.
